%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dealing%20with%20my%20children's%20lies%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20most%20challenging%20parts%20of%20parenting%20for%20me%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20little%20girl%20staring%20at%20a%20doll%20with%20a%20large%20nose%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6761e30fccd8dfcfcd7fb4f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223749%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author's%20kids%20(not%20pictured)%20have%20lied%20since%20they%20were%20young.%3Cp%3EA.%20Chederros%2FGetty%20Images%2FOnoky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20children%20have%20lied%20to%20me%20ever%20since%20they%20were%20young.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20is%20a%20normal%20part%20of%20development%20as%20kids%20test%20the%20waters%20and%20try%20to%20avoid%20punishment.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI've%20struggled%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20lying%20and%20tried%20to%20remain%20a%20positive%20role%20model%20for%20them.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20never%20ceases%20to%20amaze%20me%20how%20effortlessly%20my%20children%20lie.%20My%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-screen-time-not-worried-about-what-experts-say-effects-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E18-month-old%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20whose%20face%20was%20covered%20with%20crumbs%2C%20swore%20up%20and%20down%20that%20she%20hadn't%20been%20near%20the%20cookie%20jar.%20My%20preschooler%20looked%20me%20in%20the%20eye%20and%20denied%20breaking%20the%20window%20with%20his%20plastic%20bat%20that%20was%20still%20in%20his%20hand.%20It%20didn't%20seem%20to%20get%20better%20as%20they%20got%20older.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20handed%20my%20ATM%20card%20to%20my%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbecame-mom-forties-might-never-be-a-grandma-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoldest%20sons%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20they%20had%20money%20for%20lunch%2C%20I%20asked%20for%20the%20change%2C%20and%20they%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20only%20took%20out%20%245%2C%20so%20there%20is%20no%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20all%20know%20you%20can't%20just%20withdraw%20%245.00.%20How%20could%20they%20tell%20me%20such%20a%20bald-faced%20lie%20with%20a%20straight%20face%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDealing%20with%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flying-to-kids-effects-child-psychologist-2019-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildren's%20lies%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20most%20challenging%20aspects%20of%20parenting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb960662-e9b1-4b22-a937-8cdf3e11caf2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELying%20is%20natural%20in%20childhood%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20the%20problem%3A%20Lying%20is%20easy.%20What%20I%20find%20especially%20distressing%20is%20that%20no%20one%20has%20to%20teach%20children%20how%20to%20lie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLying%20is%20developmentally%20appropriate%2C%26quot%3B%20Ailen%20Arreaza%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20Parents%20Together%2C%20a%20national%20nonprofit%20parent%20and%20family%20advocacy%20group%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20a%20toddler%20or%20a%204-year-old%20lies%2C%20it's%20frustrating%20for%20the%20parent%2C%20but%20it's%20perfectly%20normal.%20It%20means%20that%20your%20kid's%20brain%20is%20developing%20in%20the%20way%20that%20it%20should%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArreaza%20also%20told%20me%20kids%20tell%20three%20kinds%20of%20lies%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnarcissists-are-irritating-and-attention-seeking-but-successful-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattention-seeking%3C%2Fa%3E%20ones%2C%20careless%20ones%2C%20and%20serious%20ones%20that%20happen%20when%20they're%20older.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20one%20of%20my%20sons%20told%20me%20he%20missed%20curfew%20because%20he%20lost%20track%20of%20time%20when%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20he%20was%20at%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-girlfriends-build-stunning-home-where-they-will-retire-together-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egirlfriend's%20house%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20just%20didn't%20want%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOften%20teenagers%20tell%20lies%20because%20they're%20afraid%20of%20the%20consequences%20or%20they're%20embarrassed%2C%26quot%3B%20Arreaza%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c798fed1-0c16-4d64-a31c-837cb98323f4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20struggled%20with%20how%20I%20should%20handle%20lying%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EConfronting%20my%20children%20in%20search%20of%20the%20truth%20is%20never%20comfortable.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20can%20be%20exhausting%20%E2%80%94%20a%20round-robin%20of%20questions%20and%20denials%20before%20they%20finally%20break%20and%20admit%20what%20they've%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20times%20when%20I%20was%20so%20eager%20to%20know%20the%20truth%20that%20I%20promised%20to%20refrain%20from%20any%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdocking-kids-allowance-punishment-behavior-improvement-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eform%20of%20punishment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20want%20to%20hear%20a%20confession%20to%20satisfy%20my%20suspicion%20and%20feel%20vindicated%2C%20but%20then%20I%20face%20the%20sticky%20situation%20of%20what%20happens%20next%20time%20they%20lie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20to%20address%20the%20lie%2C%20but%20not%20in%20a%20way%20that%20shames%20the%20child%20and%20labels%20them%20as%20liars%2C%26quot%3B%20Arreaza%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20about%20changing%20a%20behavior%2C%20not%20who%20the%20child%20is.%20Create%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpsychological-safety-remote-work-how-to-foster-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esafe%20environment%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20truth-telling%20is%20encouraged.%20If%20they%20think%20they're%20disappointing%20you%20or%20they'r