C%20entering%20a%20new%20phase%20of%20downturn%20that%20could%20last%20for%20years%20to%20come%2C%20a%20report%20said%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20from%20data%20industry%20provider%20CommercialEdge%20shows%20office%20vacancies%20jumped%20more%20than%205%25%20in%20six%20of%20the%20top%2025%20US%20markets%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESale%20prices%20for%20offices%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20fell%20again.%20Office%20properties%20sold%20at%20an%20average%20of%20%24179%20per%20square%20foot%2C%20down%209%25%20from%20the%20average%20sale%20price%20last%20year%2C%20though%20that%20marks%20a%20slowdown%20from%20the%2024%25%20drop%20from%202022%20to%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20offices%20are%20also%20selling%20below%20their%20previous%20transaction%20value%2C%20with%20some%20properties%20going%20for%20even%20lower%20than%20they%20did%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20construction%20was%20also%20down%20this%20year%2C%20with%20only%209.1%20million%20square%20feet%20of%20office%20space%20starting%20construction%20at%20the%20end%20of%20November%20as%20developers%20pulled%20back%20on%20most%20projects%20amid%20lower%20demand%20and%20rising%20vacancy%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommercialEdge%20says%20the%20data%20marks%20a%20new%2C%20possible%20decades-long%20phase%20of%20the%20downturn%20for%20the%20office%20sector%2C%20which%20has%20lagged%20the%20broader%20commercial%20real%20estate%20market%20recovery%20that's%20taken%20hold%20since%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20subsided.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20entered%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20'slog'%20phase%20for%20what%20we%20expect%20to%20be%20a%20multi-decade%20transformation%20of%20the%20office%20industry.%20We've%20seen%20some%20winners%20and%20we've%20seen%20some%20losers%2C%20but%20the%20threats%20of%20difficulty%20in%20refinancing%20and%20modest%20physical%20occupancy%20numbers%20remain%2C%26quot%3B%20Peter%20Kolaczynski%2C%20the%20firm's%20director%2C%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20isn't%20uniform%20across%20markets%2C%20with%20some%20that%20saw%20a%20pandemic-era%20population%20boom%20now%20struggling%20with%20too%20much%20office%20space%20after%20developers%20overbuilt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20has%20seen%20its%20vacancy%20rate%20shoot%20higher%2C%20with%20Austin%20recording%20the%20highest%20increase%20out%20of%20the%20top%2025%20US%20markets%2C%20up%206.5%25%20in%20the%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20market's%20strong%20in-migration%20and%20job%20growth%20in%20recent%20years%20have%20not%20been%20enough%20to%20offset%20the%20impact%20on%20vacancies%20of%20a%20wave%20of%20new%20supply%2C%26quot%3B%20CommercialEdge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Midwestern%20markets%20have%20the%20most%20affordable%20office%20space%20nationwide%2C%20with%20sales%20prices%20in%20Chicago%20and%20Detroit%20standing%20at%20%2497%20and%20%2480%20per%20square%20foot%2C%20respectively.%20Detroit%20recorded%20the%20lowest%20average%20sale%20price%20among%20all%20markets%20covered%20within%20the%20report%2C%20and%20the%20highest%20vacancy%20rate%20in%20the%20Midwest%20at%2025.2%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManhattan%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20continues%20to%20dominate%20sales%20volume%2C%20with%20over%20%243.8%20billion%20in%20transactions%20through%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-mandate-driving-up-home-prices-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReturn%20to%20office%20mandates%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20finance%20sector%20have%20helped%20the%20city's%20office%20market%20activity%2C%20with%20big%20purchases%20from%20firms%20like%20JPMorgan%20Chase%2C%20which%20purchased%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-07-16%2Fjpmorgan-to-buy-nyc-building-in-more-than-300-million-deal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%24320%20million%20building%20in%20Midtown%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20summer%20next%20door%20to%20another%20tower%20it's%20currently%20building.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20comes%20as%20the%20lingering%20effects%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20continue%20to%20weigh%20on%20the%20office%20sector.%20Companies%20are%20reevaluating%20their%20space%20needs%20amid%20hybrid%20work%20schedules.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20high-profile%20companies%20like%20Amazon%2C%20Dell%2C%20and%20Meta%20introduced%20stricter%20return-to-office%20mandates%20this%20year%2C%20warning%20employees%20they%20could%20face%20lower%20chances%20of%20promotion%20or%20even%20termination%20if%20they%20don't%20follow%20office%20attendance%20guidelines.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20office%20utilization%20nationwide%20appears%20largely%20unchanged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKastle%20Systems%20and%20Kisi%20Access%20Control%2C%20which%20analyzed%20aggregated%20office%20access%20data%2C%20indicated%20only%20slight%20increases%20in%20office%20usage%20throughout%20the%20year%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20estate%20market%20has%20been%20fretting%20over%20the%20state%20of%20the%20office%20sector%20since%20the%20pandemic.%20Rising%20borrowing%20costs%20and%20lower%20valuations%20have%20pressured%20the%20sector%2C%20though%20some%20other%20pros%20have%20argued%20that%20the%20worst%20may%20be%20over.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20frequently%20proposed%20option%20for%20unused%20office%20space%20has%20been%20to%20turn%20it%20into%20apartments.%20Property%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20office%20distress%20could%20lead%20to%20as%20much%20as%20a%20billion%20square%20feet%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommercial-real-estate-office-outlook-fire-sales-apartment-conversions-housing-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20apartment%20space%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsi