2title%22%3A%22Parents%20make%20more%20money%20if%20their%20kids%20are%20enrolled%20in%20universal%20pre-K%2C%20study%20finds.%20Here's%20why.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222223%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20drops%20a%20child%20off%20at%20preschool.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6570e51c7a3c8094d5da6c02%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUniversal%20pre-K%20is%20good%20for%20both%20parents%20and%20kids.%3Cp%3EFly%20View%20Productions%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20new%20study%20suggests%20universal%20pre-K%20programs%20could%20increase%20parents'%20earnings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EResearchers%20found%20that%20those%20who%20enrolled%20their%20kids%20in%20free%20pre-K%20made%20about%2021%25%20more%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUniversal%20pre-K%20programs%20have%20also%20been%20shown%20to%20help%20kids'%20long-term%20futures.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplaces-with-free-pre-k-preschool-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUniversal%20pre-K%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20long%20been%20thought%20to%20boost%20children's%20lives%20and%20futures%2C%20but%20a%20new%20study%20suggests%20parents%20could%20also%20reap%20the%20benefits%20of%20free%20and%20early%20education%20for%20their%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEconomists%20found%20that%20parents%20who%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20enroll%20their%20children%20in%20a%20universal%20pre-K%20program%20in%20Connecticut%20saw%20increased%20earnings%20by%20about%2021%25%20while%20their%20kids%20were%20in%20the%20program%2C%20as%20well%20as%20persistent%20gains%20for%20up%20to%20six%20years%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw33038%2Fw33038.pdf%3Futm_medium%3Dnewsletters%26utm_source%3Demily_essay%26utm_campaign%3D12%2F16-LatestEssay-Universal%2520PreK-Free%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20published%20in%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research%20this%20month%2C%20looked%20at%20a%20New%20Haven%20pre-K%20program%20that%20provides%20six%20and%20a%20half%20hours%20of%20free%20schooling%20each%20day%20to%20three%20and%20four-year-olds%2C%20as%20well%20as%20wraparound%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-benefits-offered-by-employers-boosts-worker-productivity-retention-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildcare%20before%20and%20after%20school.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParents%20who%20were%20lucky%20enough%20to%20win%20the%20school%20lottery%20saw%20several%20positive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fobama-economist-betsey-stevenson-affordable-childcare-student-loans-reconciliation-biden-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20researchers.%20In%20addition%20to%20increased%20wages%20over%20time%2C%20those%20whose%20kids%20enrolled%20in%20the%20program%20also%20got%20an%20average%20of%2012%20more%20working%20hours%20each%20week%2C%20the%20study%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BParents%20whose%20kids%20have%20access%20to%20reliable%2C%20high-quality%20child%20care%20in%20the%20pre-K%20period%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20work%20during%20that%20period%2C%20and%20they%20work%20more%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20economist%20Emily%20Oster%20in%20her%20ParentData%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fparentdata.org%2Fwhy-universal-pre-k-means-parents-make-more-money%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enewsletter%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThis%20extra%20work%20allows%20them%20to%20get%20on%20a%20steeper%20career%20path.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20of%20the%20study%20similarly%20chalk%20it%20up%20to%20career%20continuity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20means%20that%20%3Cem%3Eeven%20though%3C%2Fem%3E%20everyone%20eventually%20ends%20up%20working%20the%20same%20number%20of%20hours%2C%20the%20group%20that%20was%20able%20to%20invest%20in%20their%20career%20early%20have%20higher%20wages%20and%20therefore%20more%20income%2C%26quot%3B%20Oster%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20parents%20haven't%20been%20required%20to%20send%20their%20kids%20to%20school%20until%20Kindergarten%20in%20most%20states.%20But%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20municipalities%20have%20begun%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedsource.org%2Fupdates%2Fcalifornia-makes-strides-towards-universal-preschool-access%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoffering%20schooling%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20children%20as%20young%20as%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESupporters%20of%20universal%20pre-K%20say%20the%20concept%20gives%20kids%20an%20equal%20starting%20position%20heading%20into%20school%20and%20opens%20them%20up%20to%20educational%20opportunities%20at%20a%20younger%20age.%20Opponents%2C%20however%2C%20point%20to%20the%20high%20costs%20associated%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-paid-over-fifty-thousand-dollars-for-childcare-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproviding%20free%20childcare.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20studies%20in%20recent%20years%20have%20recorded%20some%20of%20the%20benefits%20for%20kids%2C%20including%202021%20research%20that%20found%20children%20who%20attended%20universal%20pre-K%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversal-pre-k-kids-more-likely-graduate-high-school-college-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20likely%20to%20graduate%20high%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20attend%20college.%20The%20study%20also%20pointed%20to%20positive%20behavioral%20impacts%20for%20those%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20positives%20go%20beyond%20academics%2C%20too.%20A%202017%20study%20found%20that%20universal%20pre-K%20helps%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversal-pre-k-health-2017-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20kids%20access%20healthcare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20earlier%20detection%20and%20treatment%20for%20conditions%20like%20asthma%20and%20hearing%20and%20vision%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAffordable%20childcare%20and%20universal%20pre-K%20could%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-could-earn-billions-more-universal-pre-k-affordable-childcare-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflush%20billions%20of%20dollars%3C%2Fa%3E%20back%20into%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20a%202022%20study%20from%20left-leaning%20think%20tank%20The%20Century%20Foundation%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%20included%20universal%20pre-K%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdemocrats-bench-build-back-better-face-obstacles-with-voting-rights-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBuild%20Back%20Better%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20failed%20to%20garner%20Congressional%20support%20back%20in%202021.%20The%20legislation%20would%20have%20allowed%20three%20million%20more%20parents%20to%20either%20enter%20the%20labor%20force%20or%20increase%20their%20working%20hours%2C%20the%20Century%20Foundation%20report%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20study%20out%20of%20New%20Haven%20notably%20did%20not%20find%20any%20evidence%20that%20universal%20pre-K%20programs%20improve%20students'%20future%20test%20scores%20%E2%80%94%20a%20finding%20in%20line%20with%20prior%20research%20that%20suggests%20the%20biggest%20benefits%20are%20more%20long-term%2C%20Oster%20noted%20in%20her%20newsletter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20end%3A%20from%20an%20economic%20standpoint%2C%20the%20biggest%20value%20to%20universal%20pre-K%20may%20be%20that%20it%20helps%20parents%20return%20to%20the%20labor%20force%20and%20make%20a%20better%20life%20for%20their%20families%20in%20the%20short%20and%20long%20run%2C%26quot%3B%20Oster%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20of%20course%2C%20that's%20also%20good%20for%20kids.%26quot%3B