Padma%20was%20quick%20to%20appreciate%20what%20my%20father's%20true%20calling%20was.%20And%20left%20no%20stone%20unturned%20in%20supporting%20and%20enabling%20him%20to%20realise%20his%20dreams.%20importantly%2C%20she%20knew%20what%20it%20took%20to%20remain%20a%20conscientious%20and%20hard-working%20judge%20and%20always%20support%20him.%20She%20was%20known%20for%20her%20pragmatism%20and%20her%20patience%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20before%20inviting%20her%20top%20court%20colleague%20to%20deliver%20the%20lecture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Nagarathna%20could%20be%20seen%20wiping%20her%20eyes%20after%20she%20resumed%20her%20seat%20on%20the%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20address%2C%20Justice%20Nagarathna%20also%20recounted%20her%20father's%20words%20when%20he%20was%20elevated%20as%20a%20judge.%20%26quot%3BA%20judge%20is%20always%20on%20trial%20and%20I%20hope%20to%20be%20acquitted%20honourably%20at%20the%20end%20of%20my%20tenure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20narrated%20an%20interesting%20anecdote%20about%20two%20lawyers%20meeting%20on%20the%20train%20--%20one%20would%20go%20on%20to%20become%20the%20President%2C%20the%20other%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20December%201946%2C%20the%20All%20India%20Lawyers'%20conference%20was%20held%20in%20Nagpur.%20Since%20there%20was%20no%20direct%20train%20between%20Bangalore%20and%20Nagpur%2C%20one%20had%20to%20go%20to%20Madras%20i.e.%20Chennai%20to%20take%20the%20Grand%20Trunk%20Express.%20In%20the%20railway%20compartment%2C%20there%20were%20a%20few%20lawyers%20travelling%20from%20Bangalore%20as%20well%20as%20Madras%20and%20everybody%20became%20friendly%20owing%20to%20shared%20interests%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BForty-three%20years%20later%2C%20in%20June%201989%2C%20two%20gentlemen%20from%20the%20railway%20compartment%20met%20at%20the%20Ashoka%20Hall%20of%20Rashtrapati%20Bhavan%2C%20one%20as%20the%20president%20of%20India%2C%20Shri%20R%20Venkata